criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Diagnosed with PD according to the primary dysmenorrhea established by Canadian
             Institute of Obstetrics and gynecology in 2005;

          2. Aged from 15 to 40 years, have not given birth, and have a history of regular
             menstrual cycles (28 days±7 days);

          3. Pain of intensity is moderate varying from 40 to 80 on the visual analogue scale
             (VAS), and lasting at least 6 months;

          4. Able to complete the baseline dysmenorrhea diary;

          5. Able to sign an informed consent

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Secondary dysmenorrhea caused by endometriosis, pelvic inflammation, myomas of uterus
             or other gynecological problems confirmed by type-B ultrasound exam by gynecologists;

          2. Have a history of pelvic or abdominal surgery, or applying oral contraceptives or
             intrauterine devices;

          3. Combined with uncontrolled diagnosed psychiatric disorders such as severe anxiety and
             depression, or severe systemic diseases affecting the implementation of treatment
             programs;

          4. Taking analgesics such as NSAIDs or having received any other treatment for PD three
             months prior to enrollment;

          5. Women in lactation, pregnant women, or those with plans to get pregnant during any
             period of the trial;

          6. Have experience of acupuncture;

          7. Illiterate, or patients unable to read and understand scales.
